mediaList.caption: Fine food and a nice atmosphere

reviews.title: A delightful dinner for three
reviews.text:
Just shared a wonderful dinner at this restaurant, where service was very friendly and attentive  and not in a rushed way. Go here if you have plenty of time to linger. Don't expect fast food. Bring your friends and family, Share all your dishes and savor & linger.

We enjoyed a delicious dinner of Chicken Tikka Masala, Chicken Tandoori and Giant Prawn Curry, raita and two kinds of Naan ( the garlic and the coconut). Everything was cooked to perfection, we loved it!

reviews.title: Dinner
reviews.text:
This is definitely one of best Indian restaurants in Rotterdam and in my opinion there are only two really good Indian restaurants in Rotterdam, this one and Curry’s in Rotterdam Kralingen. The food is authentic, tasty and fresh and the staff is very friendly.
The service is timely...just the time it takes to cook food properly. I highly recommend this restaurant!

reviews.title: Bad service and long waiting time
reviews.text:
Coming to Curry’s Centrum, we were hungrily awaiting a nice Indian meal. Within ten minutes we were able to order, yet we did notice a large group in the back. But the waiter made no mention that it could impact the amount of time it would take for the food to come. 
We ended up waiting an hour and fifteen minutes, after having asked the manager about the long waiting time. He then hastily brought half of our dishes, before we even had gotten our plates. We were missing our naans, pretty crucial to an Indian meal, as well as another dish. On the bright side, the food was tasty. However, once again, after waiting a half hour, we got our first bill, which was more than double the price of what it was supposed to be. We got sent back to the table and were forced to wait again. Only when we went up to the counter, they vaguely started paying attention to us. One of the staff was casually eating some ice cream as the manager poured himself a drink.
Finally after a whopping two and a half, we were able to leave the restaurant.

reviews.title: Excellent Indian Restaurant
reviews.text:
This restaurant is an easy walk from the city centre - around five minutes from Blaak rail/Metro and ten minutes from Rotterdam Centraal.

It is a large restaurant and table are well spaced to allow privacy.

I arrived with a friend around 7pm on a Tuesday evening and the place was quiet so easy to choose a table.

Service was very fast with drinks and snacks served while deciding on the menu.

Menu is standard Indian with a good selection of starters, main courses and desserts.

Starter of lamb and fish were very good with meat perfectly cooked and moist. Main course likewise, tender chicken cooked to perfection, rice fluffy and hotplate provided to keep the food warm during the meal.

This is a very good quality restaurant with attentive service and excellent food.

reviews.title: Very slow service, but good taste
reviews.text: The taste of the food was good and quality of the curry was also fine. However, the staff constantly forgot about us (and others) and didn't know how to run a restaurant. After asking for the bill we waited 20 minutes and then walked up to them and asked if we could pay. No sorry..... The worst things was the immense thirst we got when arriving home. We both drank 6 full glasses of water within 2 hours! Too much Ve Tsin...?

mgmtResponse.text: We like to apologize for the delayed service! Thank you that you liked our food! Hopefully, we will see you again so that you can re-experience our quality food and improved service!

reviews.title: Awesome curry's. slow but friendly service
reviews.text:
We had a lovely evening at curry's. staff is very friendly but not very fast. But if you have the time for an evening filling dinner then curry's is definitely a good option.
You get more then enough food for a reasonable price And the food tasted awesome. We also thought the spicy indication was just right.. So medium spicy was good for people who can take a bit of spice. And Hot was really hot 
There is also more then enough non-spicy food on the menu.
We took the 4-course menu. And for us is was too much. We substituted dessert for a coffee.

reviews.title: Sensational
reviews.text: My personal BEST INDIAN FOOD restaurant all over Europe! Always back there whilst in Rotterdam. Real indian food in superb location. Excellent staff! Worth a try - and a visit!

reviews.title: Amazing food
reviews.text: The food was amazing. Our waitress was very friendly and helpful. The place exceeded my expectations. A bit pricy tho...

reviews.title: Uttam Khana by Uttam
reviews.text:
Being a strict Indian vegeterian, searching for a good eating place in Europe is indeed a stressful experience.  Once in a whole, when you do come across good or great food and more importantly, combined with good service, then you are really delighted.

Yesterday, in Rotterdam, was one such day.  We are holidaying in Rotterdam and had booked an apartment through airbnb in Goudsesingel road in Rotterdam.  After a long and tiring day, we were looking for a decent Indian Restaurant and eventually landed up at Curry's centrum.  One small word of caution.  The sign board only reads as Curry's.

It was already 9 PM and there were very few customers in a rather large restaurant, and that already raised by doubts about the place.  On top of it, no one attended to us for close to ten minutes.  

I had already concluded that we were in for another lousy experience.

Then came a polite guy, started wit an apology for making us wait and took the order.  Within a few minutes his sincerity came through and we were already feeling comfortable.  He guided us through the menu and even advised us for the right portion of the orders.  

We ordered rotis, baingan barta, bhindi subzi, dal, bombay potatoes etc.,

In about ten minutes, the food started coming and within the first few bites, it was clear that the food was freshly cooked and it tasted great.  Not just because we were so hungry, but because it genuinely was cooked fresh and at 9.30 in the night...

It was a fantastic experience.  Finally, we asked for the bill and i struck a conversation with the waiter, whose name was Uttam.  It turned out that he was from Nepal, and is actually the owner of the restaurant along with his family.  

His whole family was running it together for the last few years...

We had a nice conversation.  He gave me some tips for finding inexpensive parking locations...

Overall, a great experience and will definitely go there again.

reviews.title: A major letdown
reviews.text: I found this restaurant to be poor in terms of service, choice and taste. The food reminded me of an Indian restaurant in the UK in the 1980s. Waited ages for service if that's what it's called. Lassi was the only good thing. Asked for water and I got bits in it. In summary a poor ambassador of Indian food.

Good place

reviews.title: Disappointing
reviews.text:
Having graced its sister restaurant in Kralingen on a number of occasions, and having largely enjoyed our times there, we made a point one Saturday afternoon of calling by for a late lunch. Whilst the intention seems to be more directed at the Indian buffet, we decided we wanted specific dishes, and asked whether we could indeed order freely. Told we could, we set about ordering. A vindaloo arriving at my table more akin to a bhuna, and my partner's dish being full of onions (despite asking for same either to be blitzed in the dish or left aside), and a bill that we paid simply to get our frustrated son out of the restaurant, unfortunately won't be rushing back.

A shame. Promises far more.

reviews.title: Very good food, good atmosphere !
reviews.text:
we had a lovely meal, sharing everything we ordered. It was all very tasty, delicately spiced. 
There's a new owner and a new chef, and they took the restaurant to a hole new level ! with the friendly service too, we had a very nice evening in this restaurant. I can really recommend it, after some serious shopping. Louise.

reviews.title: New ownership..going down
reviews.text:
Update: I went back to this restaurant recently and was shocked to find it really bad. The food was bad, service was average. Apparently new owners have taken over. 

The Onion pakoda was not good and all dishes were super bland. Disappointing.

Old review:
We went to this newly opened Indian restaurant. The owners were very friendly and received us warmly. They also agreed to cook something not on the menu.

Food was very tasty. We ordered a wonderful mango lassi and then ordered chana masala and panner saag for mains. Extremely tasty food.

We went back a couple of more times during our stay.
